      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can repot your fiddle leaf fig by first placing a fresh, well-draining mix into the new pot, then carefully lifting the plant and gently loosening the roots before setting it in the center. Use a soil blend that is loose and airy, such as a mix of peat moss, perlite, and orchid bark, which allows roots to breathe and prevents compaction. After filling the pot, water lightly to settle the soil and monitor the plant for a week to ensure there are no signs of shock.",
